{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The following ranges for the number of vertices were considered: 6 ≤ n ≤ 26 for 2-paths, 8 ≤ n ≤ 19 for 3-paths, and 8 ≤ n ≤ 18 for 4-paths.",
    "These lists were used, extensively, to obtain information about the behavior of the eigenvalues of the Laplacian and the A α -matrices.",
    "As a result of this work, given fixed n ≥ k + 1 and a bounded n, it was possible to identify the structure of the k-path graph that maximizes or minimizes the algebraic connectivity, and maximizes the α-index, and the second largest eigenvalue of A α (G) (λ 2 (A α)), for α ∈ {0.1,..., 0.9}.",
    "Finally, two conjectures were proposed regarding the mentioned eigenvalues.It is worth mentioning that all the experimental results obtained in this work for 2-path and 3-path graphs are consistent with the theorems and conjectures set in [24] and [25] for outerplanar and planar graphs.",
    "However, 4-path graphs are non-planar, and to our knowledge, do no exist other works in the literature about extremal graphs for the algebraic connectivity or αindex of k-path graphs with k ≥ 4.The obtained results allow identifying research problems to be addressed."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Finally, two conjectures were proposed regarding the mentioned eigenvalues.It is worth mentioning that all the experimental results obtained in this work for 2-path and 3-path graphs are consistent with the theorems and conjectures set in [24] and [25] for outerplanar and planar graphs."
  ]
}